injuries.longComment: Herro is coming off the best season of his NBA career, averaging career-high numbers in points (23.9), assists (5.5) and steals (0.9) while also shooting a career-high 47.2 percent from the field. The Kentucky product's absence will likely result in more playing time for Davion Mitchell and Kasparas Jakucionis in the backcourt to begin the 2025-26 campaign. Miami newcomer Norman Powell will probably be leaned on to pick up the slack offensively, with the team's most talented scorer sidelined potentially until mid-November.
injuries.shortComment: Herro (foot/ankle) is expected to take eight weeks to recover after undergoing successful surgery Friday, Shams Charania of ESPN reports.

items.headline: Herro (foot/ankle) is expected to take eight weeks to recover after undergoing successful surgery Friday, Shams Charania of ESPN reports.

injuries.longComment: Larsson's 24-point performance in Monday's win against the Celtics will be his last appearance during the Las Vegas Summer League. The Arizona product played well during his stint in Las Vegas, scoring 14 points or more in each game he played while shooting 50 percent from the floor.
injuries.shortComment: Larsson (not injury related) has played his last game during this Las Vegas Summer League, Anthony Chiang of the Miami Herald reports.

injuries.longComment: Smith will return to Miami on a standard deal after spending the majority of the first three years of his career with the organization. The 27-year-old guard missed most of the 2023-24 campaign due to a torn ACL and appeared in only 14 regular-season games during the 2024-25 season before undergoing season-ending surgery to repair a ruptured left Achilles tendon in December. In those 14 appearances (one start), he averaged 6.2 points, 2.6 rebounds, 1.6 assists and 1.5 steals across 19.1 minutes per game. Smith will likely continue to operate as a backcourt reserve for Miami, though it remains unclear whether he'll be cleared to return by Opening Night.
injuries.shortComment: Smith agreed to a three-year, $7.9 million deal with the Heat on Saturday, Michael Scotto of USA Today reports.

injuries.longComment: Rozier will miss his sixth straight outing Monday due to a sprained left ankle. There's no clear timetable for the veteran guard's return, though his absence shouldn't cause any major waves in Miami's rotation.
injuries.shortComment: Rozier (ankle) has been ruled out for Monday's Game 4 against Cleveland.
